## 1. mbuzz — Best for Validated Attribution

**Why consider mbuzz:** Ruler Analytics shows attribution. mbuzz proves it with incrementality testing.

### What mbuzz Offers

**Server-side tracking for lead generation.** While Ruler Analytics focuses on call + web tracking with client-side methods, mbuzz tracks on your backend—capturing 95%+ of form submissions and web events that ad blockers hide.

**8 attribution models for multi-touch lead gen.** Compare First Touch (who found you?), Last Touch (what converted them?), Linear, Time Decay, U-Shaped, W-Shaped, plus data-driven Markov Chain and Shapley Value. See which model best reflects your lead-to-customer journey.

**Custom attribution rules for service businesses.** Weight touchpoints by lead quality, service type, or conversion value:

```ruby
# Service business: Weight high-value service inquiries
model "lead_quality_weighted" do
  if conversion_type == "consultation_request"
    weight 1.5
  elsif channel == "referral"
    weight 1.25
  elsif channel == "paid_search" && keyword.service_related?
    weight 1.0
  else
    weight :time_decay
  end
end
```

**Closed-loop revenue attribution.** Track beyond the lead—connect to your CRM to attribute actual revenue, not just form fills. See which campaigns drive clients who pay, stay, and refer.

**Pricing without the £349/mo entry:**

