## Call Tracking + Attribution: Integrated vs. Separate

You have two architectural choices:

```
Option 1: Integrated (Ruler Analytics approach)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Pros:
├── Single tool, single vendor
├── Pre-integrated data
├── Simpler setup
└── Unified reporting

Cons:
├── May not be best-in-class at either
├── Vendor lock-in
└── Less flexibility


Option 2: Separate (mbuzz + CallRail approach)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Pros:
├── Best-in-class at each function
├── Flexibility to swap components
├── Deeper capabilities per tool
└── Can add incrementality (mbuzz)

Cons:
├── Integration required
├── Multiple vendors
├── More complex setup
└── Higher total cost potentially
```

For most businesses, the question is: **How important is call tracking vs. attribution accuracy?**

- Calls are primary → CallRail/Invoca + lighter attribution
- Attribution accuracy is primary → mbuzz + call tracking integration

